  "The United States and India": "",
  "The United States and the Soviet Union": "",
  "The United States and China": "",
  "Europe and Japan": "",
  "The Space Race was a Cold War-era competition between the United States and the Soviet Union from the late 1950s through the early 1970s, driven by national prestige and ideological rivalry.": "",
  "The first American in space was:": "",
  "Buzz Aldrin": "",
  "Alan Shepard became the first American in space on May 5, 1961, with a 15-minute suborbital flight aboard the Freedom 7 capsule as part of the Mercury program.": "",
  "The Space Shuttle program operated from:": "",
  "1990 to 2020": "",
  "1957 to 1975": "",
  "1969 to 2000": "",
  "1981 to 2011": "",
  "NASA's Space Shuttle program ran from 1981 to 2011, completing 135 missions and serving as the world's first reusable crewed spacecraft system for launching satellites, building the ISS, and conducting research.": "",
  "The total number of people who have walked on the Moon is:": "",
  "24": "",
  "2": "",
  "6": "",
